A truck and a Volkswagen
Golf were involved in an accident on the N1 North after the Maraisburg Bridge, in
Mooifontein. According
to Netcare 911 spokesperson Shawn Herbst said reports from the scene indicate
that the car and truck were involved in a collision. “Paramedics
assessed the scene and found that two occupants of the car had sustained
moderate injuries and were treated on scene by Advanced Life support paramedics,”
he said. Herbst added
that once stabilised both patients were transported by private ambulance to a
hospital for further treatment.     